title: Weddings
name: Weddings
body:
Your wedding day is one of the most precious days of your life, so when you sit down to view your wedding photographs, I want you to truly feel as though you have been transported back to your special day and a flood of memories come rushing back with every photo you see. It means you will always be able to re live your magical day!

I absolutely love capturing those precious moments between the two of you, from a hearty giggle during the speeches to a teary look of pure joy as you say your vows. The cake will get eaten and the flowers will die, but your photos will last forever. That's why I believe photography is not only amazing but essential too.

What's important to me is capturing emotions that will be frozen in time forever. Those special moments between the two of you, and your family and friends, are so precious and should always be cherished. These specials images can be admired for years to come, so the moments and emotions of the big day will never be forgotten.

My style is very natural, and my aim is to be as discreet as possible and to blend into the background. I truly believe that people look their best when they forget the camera is there, and they are at their most natural and relaxed.

I am a perfectionist in my work and truly want to give you the best possible photos of the most magical day, that bring back the happiness, laughter and memories whenever you look at them! I always look for the best light and backdrops throughout the day, creating for you beautiful photos that will last a lifetime.

I always feel very privileged and excited at the prospect of covering more beautiful weddings here in Jersey, Guernsey, France and further afield.

posts.title: Ellen & Alex
posts.body:
Ellen chose to get ready at her parents house in Grouville and was then driven to the castle in her father's Jaguar. Ellen's hair and make up was done by the fantastic Lauren Layzell. The outdoor ceremony at Mont Orgueil castle took place above the chapel, overlooking Gorey bay, with France in the distance.

Ellen and Alex's reception was at one of my favourite venues in Jersey, St.Ouen's Manor. With peacocks roaming free on the manor's grounds and a marquee in the walled garden full of lavender and flowers, it really is a picturesque venue.

The marquee was decorated by Mark Howe using whimsical English summer flowers, a forest of silver birch and dozens of candles and it looked beautiful. Ellen and Alex were such a fun and relaxed couple which you can clearly see in the photos, it really was an amazing day.

posts.title: India and Alistair
posts.body:
India and Alistair's wedding took place in August on a lovely summer's day. India, her bridesmaids and her family got ready at their stunning family home in St Peter's.

One of my favourite photos is of India, so elegant, taking a last look at herself in the mirror before heading to the church. These split second moments are what I look to capture.

India and her father were picked up in a 1928 Willys Whippet open tourer which took them to the ceremony at St Peter's parish church. La Mare Wine Estate was the chosen reception venue, a wonderful place full of photo opportunities. The guests enjoyed  Champagne on the lawn, followed by an excellent meal by Jersey Potteries.

Another of my favourite shots is of India's father looking at his daughter during the speeches, his pride is clear. This will be a precious photo for India that captures a special moment between them.

Deborah, India's mother helped plan the day to perfection, down to every detail, and because of this, the occasion ran so smoothly and was such a success.

I almost felt like part of the family by the end of the day, and everyone made me feel so welcome. I was still buzzing from it in the weeks after the wedding.

posts.title: Steph & Andy
posts.body:
Steph and Andy's beautiful summer wedding took place at St.Brelades Bay Church in Jersey, a pretty historic church overlooking the sea. Steph and her bridesmaids had their make-up beautifully applied by Decia from Kiss and Make up. The hairstylist of choice was the talented Sophie-Lee Kelly from Hatleys. During their ceremony, they couldn't stop smiling throughout! Steph looked beautiful in her La Sposa wedding dress from the Bridal Boutique. 

The Marquee Solutions marquee at Bayview, a pretty field overlooking St.Ouen's Bay, was decorated by Eden By Claire, it looked amazing! The delicious wedding cake was created by Flour bakery. Andy’s father is a bee keeper here in Jersey and even supplied the honey for the favours, a lovely touch! Andy’s mother’s family are well known as Jersey Royal farmers and supplied the potatoes for the wedding breakfast, cooked by the caterers of choice, Jersey Kitchen. Guests enjoyed canapés and Champagne on the lawn overlooking the panoramic views of St.Ouen's Bay. 

Everybody was ready to party into the night after Steph & Andy took to the dance floor for their first dance. The newly Mr and Mrs De Carteret even went for a sunset stroll together in the meadow, what a moment! Thank you Steph and Andy, I'm so pleased I was a part of your incredible day!

posts.title: Becky & Karl
posts.body:
Becky and Karl's beautiful summer wedding took place at the idyllic Samares Manor in Jersey. Their outdoor ceremony commenced in the lush and fragrant manor's gardens in front of their friends and families. Becky looking beautiful in her Pronovias wedding dress from Ellis Bridal Collections.

The Marquee Solutions marquee looked stunning and was decorated by Eden By Claire and Style to Cherish. The pretty flower wall and donut stand were supplied by Sweet P Creations. Becky and her bridesmaids had their make-up beautifully applied by India Ball. The caterers of choice were Niche Events. Guests enjoyed canapés and champagne on the lawn in front of the Manor.

The speeches had guests full of all emotions and everybody was ready to party into the night after Mr and Mrs Gorin took to the dance floor for their first dance. What a day!

posts.title: Sarah & Fabien
posts.body:
Sarah and Fabien married on a beautiful summers day in the St.Lawrence Parish Church. The reception was held at Sarah's family's private home in the countryside. Once the sun had set, the espresso Martinis came out and the DJ really got the party started. 

The newly married Mr and Mrs Sacriste danced the night away once the sun had set and the guests were wowed at the end of the night with a firework display. Thank you Sarah and Fabien for sharing your amazing day with me!
